Let's see if i'm right Kendrick... (hope this doesn't break the express written "no addressing the Verant peeps" rule)<br>
<br>
Instead of increasing the size of the hate list by increasing the size of the hate list's array, they added more arrays, (probably 9 more arrays, to bring the total to 10 arrays, of size 1-6, yes?)  So, what your proposed evade change does is this:<br>
<br>
Drops the evading rogue to between the 2nd-3rd person on their group's array, and not between 2 and 3 on the ENTIRE array.  This makes sense, and if your tests aren't showing 6 dead rogues all the time within the first 20 seconds of combat, then that must be how the hate list was lengthened.  <br>
<br>
Single group example:<br>
Warrior, ranger, rogue, shaman, wizard, enchanter<br>
<br>
<table><font size=1><br>
<td width=250 valign=top align=left><br>
Group hatelist (pre evade)<br>
1. Rogue<br>
2. Warrior<br>
3. Ranger<br>
4. Shaman<br>
5. Wizard<br>
6. Enchanter<br>
</td><br>
<td width=250 valign=top align=left><br>
Group hatelist (post evade)<br>
1. Warrior<br>
2. Rogue (dropped to between 2 and 3)<br>
3. Ranger<br>
4. Shaman<br>
5. Wizard<br>
6. Enchanter<br>
</td></font><br>
</table><br>
<br>
Ok, so this is fine with everyone (I would have rather seen the rogue dropped between the shaman ranger and the shaman personally (3rd and 4th people, not the 2nd and 3rd), but I can deal.<br>
<br>
Now, to imagine how this applies to multiple group raids.  Imagine 6 groups (all of that same make up).  Now, what happens? The way that the arrays work, each rogue is evading down the array in his OWN GROUP, as opposed to evading down the array in THE ENTIRE HATE LIST.  So, you always evade down the list in your own group's hatelist.  The group with the highest hate is the group that's getting beat on, and the person in the group with agro with the highest hate is going to be the one recieving the brunt of the attack.<br>
<br>
There you have it.  Kendrick, if you had simply explained the expanded hate list, and how it worked to us, I doubt there would have been conflict at all.  Definately would have saved me the headache of fuggin' trying to figure out how the hell you could have gone from being a good guy to lower than low.  Now i'm wondering if you even understood what the hell we were even talking about, evading down to 10-12th on the list (since that would require something that the current hate list does not directly support). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ul0z.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L0z</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/lozdarogue/Rbsmall.JPG BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 2/9/01 5:31:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uromtomshinkicker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Romtom  Shinkicker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/01 3:26:50 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ninedotnine.com/legions/gallery/romclaw.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zen and the Art of Evade Mechanics</span><hr size=1> speak for yourself gyorg, not for others <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrick>Kendrick</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grandfather Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/01 6:29:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zen and the Art of Evade Mechanics</span><hr size=1> Actually Loz, it's now one array of 60, not 10 arrays of 6. I guess I'm still lower than low, eh?<br>
