<br>
If there were only two people in the zone, I would guess that if you were number one on the hate list, you'd be put somewhere behind your parnter, or have 500 hate deducted - whichever is greater.  Since the formula calls for being put behind the second place person on the hate list, I don't think it should be a problem.<br>
<br>
In fact, the formula may default to considering the third (non-existent) person as having zero hate, meaning a big (over 50 percent) deduction in hate.<br>
