<br>
Well, if you look at it closer you'll see that monks and rogues are supposed to do the highest melee damage. However, monks do more damage, they have more hp than rogues, but the poison skill compensates this. Accepted.<br>
<br>
Monks have a skill(feign death) which clears their aggro points completely. In addition to that, it make the monster believe the monk is dead, so it wanders off or jumps onto the 2nd of the hate list. This allows the monk to controll his damage output. One feign death, grands that he will never get back to the top of the list again.<br>
<br>
Now I'll come to the point:<br>
<br>
By creating a class that requires to attack from behind to deal the damage, that it is supposed to deal, you created a dangerous thing.<br>
That means, when the mob turns around and starts to hit the rogue, the rogue will loose a significant amount of his damage output, every time, while every other class in EQ will do exactly the same damage, no matter if the opponent faces them or not.<br>
The rogue will do less damage than a warrior, has lower ac and hp, so he will be totally replaced by a warrior, and that's true. If a rogue does less damage in any fight than a warrior, this class is totally useless, I mean when it comes to choose the class, sure it still does damage. Therefore touching evade is a unbelievable dangerous thing.<br>
<br>
The rogue should never ever be top of the hate list, as you see from my statements above, no other melee class requires not to get hit as much as the rogues do because this touches his damage output.<br>
<br>
Monks can reduce their aggro by 100% and they get 2 things, they can play death so they are great pullers.<br>
The only thing to fix rogues will be to give them a 85%(not 100% because we get poison) hate reduction.<br>
<br>
Well I know this sounds like ooh ohh look how few points he has now, but please consider again, the rogue is the only melee dealing class, that requires not to be top of the hate list to do what he was created for.<br>
I hope you understand what my concerns are. <br>
Agro controlling isn't as important for any class as it is for the rogue class.<br>
<br>
One last comment for the current changes(2nd on the hate list, atleast -500 hatepoints). Stop and play a warrior, monk.<br>
<br>
Flalmer<br>
Lvl 51 Rake, Lvl 56 Preserver<br>
