<br>
I was doing some scouting around (while sneaking/hiding of course) and was having absolutely NO problems.  Everything conned indifferent to me and I had moved pretty deep into the level and well past the keyholder mob for that level (the Genie).  Suddenly for no apparent reason, I go LD and drop to the server selection screen.  I have not gone LD in months and I have a very reliable cable connection.  The fact that I dropped to the server connection screen is suggestive that my ISP did not drop me, but rather one of the countless LD's that seems to be ocouring on The Rathe nearly every evening and weekend.  <br>
<br>
Ok..so what u say?  Well when I logged back in I was shocked to find that I had apparently died and was back at my bind point naked as a baby.  I of course petitioned the GM and was told that there was NO WAY that the LD was Sony's fault and that under no circumstances could there be anything wrong with the servers to have caused my LD.  I was also told that when going LD that hide/sneak will of course cease to function and thus if you are in the middle of a mob, you will likely be killed.  <br>
<br>
The point of this whole thing is this.  The GM's did not want to accept any responsibility for any fault regarding my LD, and I didnt want to accept any responsibility either given that I was having NO problems doing what is definately in character for our class.  I absolutely feel that if Sneak/Hide were persistant across zones and when logging out and back in that this would not have been any problem at all.  After all, invis persists both through zones and when camping and through LD.  The unfortunate incident caused me and my group a WHOLE LOT of down time (those that have died in the upper levels of the tower know what I'm talking about) and about 300 plat for a rez.  <br>
<br>
So, in closing Sony/Verant if you don't want to accept responsibility for the LD's that are ocouring with increased frequency, then please take the time and make the effort to change the code to allow us to have persistant hide/sneak.  And at a minimum.....if you are going to insist that you dont have the time required to make the code changes...change your &quot;policies&quot; to allow GM's to provide assistance to people like me who have suffered from a technical problem rather than in-game incompetence.  This means at a MINIMUM...and corpse summon if needed if not an out and out rez.  We pay you good money to play your game.  Why would you ever want to see us be frustrated in this way? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukyojitsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyojitsu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 10:16:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lyion_sp/term.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why hide/sneak should persist</span><hr size=1> Kendrick,<br>
